<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-5232] ALTER TABLE ADD - data loss</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5232</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;cqlsh:Test&amp;gt; CREATE TABLE t1 (id int PRIMARY KEY, t text);&lt;br/&gt;
cqlsh:Test&amp;gt; UPDATE t1 SET t = &apos;111&apos; WHERE id = 1;&lt;br/&gt;
cqlsh:Test&amp;gt; ALTER TABLE t1 ADD l list&amp;lt;text&amp;gt;;&lt;br/&gt;
cqlsh:Test&amp;gt; SELECT * FROM t1;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; id | l    | t&lt;br/&gt;
---&lt;del&gt;&lt;ins&gt;&lt;/del&gt;----&lt;del&gt;&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/del&gt;----&lt;br/&gt;
  1 | null | 111&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cqlsh:Test&amp;gt; ALTER TABLE t1 ADD m map&amp;lt;int, text&amp;gt;;&lt;br/&gt;
cqlsh:Test&amp;gt; SELECT * FROM t1;&lt;br/&gt;
cqlsh:Test&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Last query doesn&apos;t return any data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
